Raw dev notes -- Building a Hebrew News Article Extractor (Feb-March 2026)

Built a web service that extracts clean article text from Israeli news websites.
Started with a handful of sites, now supports 17 including major outlets.
Deployed on Google Cloud Run.

The journey:
- Started with an off-the-shelf extraction library but it fails on many Hebrew sites
- Built per-site CSS selector chains with fallback strategies
- Each site is a special snowflake: different content models, AMP pages, paywalled content
- Had to handle various anti-bot protections on some sites

Deployment challenges:
- Cloud Run cold starts are annoying but acceptable for the use case
- Some sites actively block requests from cloud/datacenter IPs
- Tried multiple approaches: custom headers, proxy services, alternative endpoints
- A few sites remain limited -- accepting that as a tradeoff

Did two full rounds of selector audits across all supported sites.
Found and fixed extraction bugs affecting about half of them.

The hardest part isn't the initial extraction -- it's maintenance. Sites redesign,
change their markup, add new protection layers. Each new site is a mini
reverse-engineering project.

Next: Custom domain, more sites, possibly a browser extension version.
